sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sam8sam5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Both genes are derived from Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 4429.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of the genes sam8 and sam5, encoding tyrosine ammonia lyase and 4-coumarate-3-hydroxylase, from the bacterium Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 4429. The enzymes acting together are expected to convert tyrosine to caffeic acid. Reference: Berner, M., Krug, D., Bihlmaier, C., Vente, A., Muller, R. and Bechthold, A. 'Genes and Enzymes Involved in Caffeic Acid Biosynthesis in the Actinomycete Saccharothrix espanaensis' J. Bacteriol. 188 (7), 2666-2673 (2006). Note that there is a PstI site near the 3' end of the sam5 gene in this version. This will be removed by site directed mutagenesis in due course. This construct was prepared to test activity before undertaking the mutagenesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note that this version of sam5 contains a PstI site near the 3' end. Thus this biobrick was prepared by inserting sam8 (EcoRI-SpeI) upstream of sam5 (EcoRI-XbaI) to avoid cutting with PstI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rbs+sam5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sam5 (4-coumarate-3-hydroxylase) of the bacterium Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 44229 with its native rbs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This was made as a single biobrick, rather than separate rbs and coding sequence, hence the use of blunt ligation in generating this composite part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rbs+sam8
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: sam8 (tyrosine ammonia lyase) with native rbs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is sam8 (tyrosine ammonia lyase) of the bacterium Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 44229 with its native ribosome binding site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was made as a single biobrick rather than separate rbs and coding sequence, hence the use of blunt ligation in generating the final sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sam5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 44229, sequence accession ABC88666.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of sam5, encoding 4-coumarate-3-hydroxylase from the bacterium Saccharothrix espanaensis. The enzyme converts p-coumaric acid to caffeic acid. Accession: ABC88666. Reference: Berner, M., Krug, D., Bihlmaier, C., Vente, A., Muller, R. and Bechthold, A. 'Genes and Enzymes Involved in Caffeic Acid Biosynthesis in the Actinomycete Saccharothrix espanaensis' J. Bacteriol. 188 (7), 2666-2673 (2006). Note: contains a PstI site. This will be removed by site directed mutagenesis in due course but is still present, near the 3' end, in this version.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note that this version of the gene contains a PstI site near the 5' end. This will ultimately be removed by site directed mutagenesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: sam8
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of sam8, encoding tyrosine ammonia lyase, from the bacterium Saccharothrix espanaensis DSM 4429. The enzyme converts tyrosine to p-coumaric acid. Accession: ABC88666. Reference: Berner, M., Krug, D., Bihlmaier, C., Vente, A., Muller, R. and Bechthold, A. 'Genes and Enzymes Involved in Caffeic Acid Biosynthesis in the Actinomycete Saccharothrix espanaensis' J. Bacteriol. 188 (7), 2666-2673 (2006)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Virtual part to be added to coding sequence I742142.
